thread.title: Two killed in 'horrific' car crash north of Brisbane
thread.title_full: Two killed in 'horrific' car crash north of Brisbane

author: Matt Eaton
title: Two killed in 'horrific' car crash north of Brisbane
text:
Map: Deception Bay 4508 
A young woman and man have been killed when their car crashed head-on into a power pole at high speed north of Brisbane this morning. 
Queensland Fire and Emergency Services Superintendent Andrew Bailey said emergency services were confronted with "a horrific traffic accident" at Bayview Terrace, at Deception Bay. 
The car was completely wrapped around the power pole and the force of the impact was strong enough to throw the car's engine several metres clear of the wreckage. 
There was nothing authorities could do for the two people inside. 
"Emergency services, between ambulance, police and fire have done their very best, unfortunately the situation is that there are two deceased persons," Superintendent Bailey said. 
Police said the car lost control as it came around a bend on Park Road near an intersection just before 3:30am. 
It took police and fire crews about an hour to remove the car from the pole and pull the wreckage apart to extract the victims' bodies. 
Superintendent Bailey said power had to be cut to nearby homes as they worked to remove the car from the pole. 
He said it was a confronting sight for all involved at the scene. 
"Our men and women have to be very, very strong when it comes to this sort of incident," he said. 
"I think at any time there's a fatality its one of horrid things that can actually happen and that is the trauma that all of the emergency services, particularly QFES, put up on a daily basis."
